'''Accessories''' are cosmetic elements that can be placed on any usable [[avatar]]. Accessories are managed from the '''Accessories''' section of the [[Avatar]] tab and are separate from the [[Inventory]]. Up to 5 accessories can be placed on a single avatar at a time.

Unlike [[Items]], accessories have no scripting, are not interactable, and travel with the user between [[worlds]] without needing to be spawned in. Worlds cannot restrict accessory usage.

VRChat creates accessories internally and collaborates with select community creators.

== Overview ==
When a user adds an accessory to their avatar, it is automatically attached to a default [[avatar]] bone (such as the head, hips, or arm) chosen to best suit the accessory. Users can reassign the accessory to any bone on the avatar's skeleton through the attachment controls.

Each accessory can be repositioned, rotated, and scaled using on-screen controls or the precise adjustment panel on the right side of the editor. Some accessories also offer additional customization options, such as color changes or toggling visual elements. Accessories use VRChat's Toon Standard shader.

== Looks ==
A '''Look''' is a saved combination of accessories and a specific avatar. When an accessory is added to an avatar for the first time, VRChat automatically creates a new Look. Users can create and manage multiple Looks from the '''Looks''' section of the [[Avatar]] tab, allowing quick switching between different accessory combinations.

===Editor===
The Looks Editor is how users can add and customize accessories on their avatar. It is spilt up into 3 sections: 

* '''Left''': This side displays all owned accessories. Clicking on an accessory will add it to the avatar and assign it to a default bone. Hovering over an added accessory allow the user the option to duplicate it. Additionally, an undo, redo, and reset buttons are under the owned accessories.

* '''Right''': This side displays all properties of the selected accessory. An accessory can have its position, rotation, and scale edited. Some accessories have additional customizable properties, such as toggles, colors, or blend shapes.

* '''Middle''': The section showcases your avatar with its accessories. When an accessory is selected, the camera will focus onto the accessory and show a gizmo depends on if the user is editing its position, rotation, or scale. At the bottom of the editor, the camera orientation can be changed by toggle between "Front" & "Top".<br><br>When the position header is selected, the parent bone can be edited on the right side. Once clicked, the avatar will go transparent and display all human bones by default. The green bone is the bone that the accessory is currently applied to, and the white bones are bones that can be selected. The displayed bones can be changed by clicking "Human" at the bottom of the editor, it will show all "Extra" bones that an accessory can be applied to.

